race.description: The Sporting Globe Last Call (Mcc Series Heat) Hcp
race.comment: Siding with FLYING VALLEY (5) in the final. He won two in a row prior to last start when pitched way out of his depth in the G2 Feehan Stakes behind Pride Of Jenni & Treasurethe Moment. That wasn't a bad effort when beaten 7 lengths and his prior form has him hard to beat. JENNI THE FOX (11) also drops a fair way in grade having contested a pair of G2 mare's races at her past two. She was only 3 lengths off Abounding last time who won at Caulfield on Saturday. Shinn goes on to offset the wide draw. FRIDGE MONSTER (10) is flying having won his past two. This is harder but he's always promised a bit. AMBASSADORIAL (12) has been thereabouts his past two without much luck last time. He'll roll forward and give a sight.
